WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
Welcome! Your Connect course will have activities that will require you to speak in the target language using a microphone.

1
00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:16.000
This tutorial is designed to ensure that your system is compatible, you're able to set up your microphone,

2
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:19.000
and that you can complete these activities successfully.

3
00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:25.000
For these activities, you can use a desktop, a laptop, or if you choose to use a tablet,

4
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.000
use the Connect app or a web browser.

5
00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:29.000
Please make sure your web browser is compatible.

6
00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:37.100
web browser is compatible. It is recommended to use Mozilla Firefox, Google Chrome, or Microsoft Edge to complete your activities on a PC.

7
00:00:37.940 --> 00:00:44.500
The Safari browser may also be used if you're working on a tablet. You should now be prepared to begin your exercises.

8
00:00:45.220 --> 00:00:54.720
When beginning your first recording exercise, once you hit record My Voice, you'll be prompted to allow McGraw-Hill access to your microphone so that your answers can be recorded.

9
00:00:54.720 --> 00:00:58.720
Please allow access and then answer the question.

10
00:00:58.720 --> 00:01:02.720
When your answer is complete, click on Stop Recording.

11
00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:04.720
Now you have a few options.

12
00:01:04.720 --> 00:01:09.720
You can play your recording to make sure you like how you've pronounced the words or answer the question.

13
00:01:09.720 --> 00:01:13.720
If you want to try again, you can re-record your answer.

14
00:01:13.720 --> 00:01:17.720
If you're satisfied with your recording, you can save it to be graded.

15
00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:22.720
Remember to submit your assignment after you have saved the recording.

16
00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:30.600
If you still have questions or concerns, please contact McGraw-Hill support, which is always available from the main Connect screen.